==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lussheburgh
<hw>Lus"she*burgh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A spurious coin
of light weight imported into England from <etsep>Luxemburg</etsep>, or
Lussheburgh, as it was formerly called.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God wot, no <qex>Lussheburghes</qex> payen ye.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lust</ent>⟦br⟧
